Wash and dry all produce. Preheat the oven to 400 degrees. Bring a large #pot
of salted water to a boil. Halve, peel, and finely chop the @yellow onion{1}(halved,
peeled, and finely chopped). Mince or grate the @garlic{2%cloves}(minced or grated).
Tear the @fresh mozzarella{4%oz} into small pieces. Remove and discard the @kale{4%oz}
ribs and stems before coarsely chopping the leaves. Pick then coarsely chop the
@basil{1/2%oz}(picked and coarsely chopped).

Boil the fusilli: Add the @fusilli pasta{6%oz} to the boiling water. Cook
~{9-11%minutes}, until al dente. Drain.

Meanwhile, heat a large drizzle of @olive oil{2%teaspoon} in a large pan over
medium heat. Add the onions. Cook, tossing, for ~{4-5%minutes}, until softened.
Add the @ground beef{10%oz}, garlic, @dried oregano{1%teaspoon}, and as many
@chili flakes{1%teaspoon} as you like. Break up the meat into pieces, until browned.

Cook the kale: Add the kale to the #pan. Toss ~{3-4%minutes}, until wilted. Add a
splash of @water{}, if necessary, to help it wilt. Season with @salt{} and @pepper{}.

In a large #bowl, combine the fusilli, basil, beef mixture, @crushed tomatoes{1%box},
and half the mozzarella cheese. Season with salt and pepper.

Transfer the fusilli mixture to a lightly oiled #baking dish{} (ours is 9"x9").
Sprinkle with the @panko breadcrumbs{1/4%cup} and remaining mozzarella cheese.
Place in the oven for ~{8-10%minutes}, until browned and bubbling. Enjoy!